- name: klipper_sdk_orchestration
  description: Orchestrates the development of the Klipper clipboard manager SDK.
  goal: "Develop a comprehensive SDK for the Klipper clipboard manager."
  planes:
    structural:
      - name: define_sdk_requirements
        description: Define the functional and non-functional requirements for the Klipper SDK.
        goal: "Establish a clear and comprehensive set of requirements for the Klipper SDK."
        steps:
          - name: gather_functional_requirements
            description: Collect all necessary functional features for the SDK.
            goal: "Identify and document all core functionalities of the Klipper SDK."
            agent: GPTASe
          - name: gather_non_functional_requirements
            description: Collect all necessary non-functional aspects (performance, security, etc.) for the SDK.
            goal: "Identify and document all non-functional requirements for the Klipper SDK."
            agent: TASe
          - name: consolidate_requirements
            description: Combine functional and non-functional requirements into a single document.
            goal: "Create a unified requirements document for the Klipper SDK."
            agent: uTASe
          - name: purify_requirements
            description: Refine and validate the consolidated requirements for clarity and completeness.
            goal: "Ensure the requirements are unambiguous, complete, and feasible."
            agent: puTASe
      - name: design_sdk_architecture
        description: Design the overall architecture of the Klipper SDK.
        goal: "Create a robust and scalable architecture for the Klipper SDK."
        dependencies:
          - define_sdk_requirements
        steps:
          - name: propose_architectural_patterns
            description: Identify and propose suitable architectural patterns for the SDK.
            goal: "Select appropriate architectural patterns that align with SDK requirements."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: define_api_interfaces
            description: Define the public API interfaces for the SDK.
            goal: "Specify clear and well-documented API endpoints for SDK users."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: design_data_models
            description: Design the data models and structures for the SDK.
            goal: "Establish efficient and consistent data representations within the SDK."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: create_ui_ux_flows
            description: Design the user interface and user experience flows for any associated UI components.
            goal: "Develop intuitive and visually appealing UI/UX for Klipper SDK integrations."
            agent: Aurora
      - name: implement_sdk
        description: Implement the Klipper SDK based on the defined architecture and requirements.
        goal: "Develop a functional and high-quality Klipper SDK."
        dependencies:
          - design_sdk_architecture
        steps:
          - name: set_up_development_environment
            description: Configure the necessary tools and environments for SDK development.
            goal: "Establish a productive and efficient development setup."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: develop_core_modules
            description: Implement the core functionalities of the SDK.
            goal: "Build the foundational components of the Klipper SDK."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: implement_api_endpoints
            description: Implement the defined API interfaces.
            goal: "Translate API interface designs into functional code."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: integrate_ui_components
            description: Integrate the designed UI/UX components.
            goal: "Incorporate the visual and interactive elements into the SDK."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: write_unit_tests
            description: Write comprehensive unit tests for all implemented modules.
            goal: "Ensure code quality and identify defects early."
            agent: Kodax
      - name: test_and_refine_sdk
        description: Test the implemented SDK and refine based on feedback.
        goal: "Ensure the SDK is stable, performant, and meets all requirements."
        dependencies:
          - implement_sdk
        steps:
          - name: conduct_integration_testing
            description: Test the integration of different SDK modules.
            goal: "Verify seamless interaction between SDK components."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: perform_performance_testing
            description: Evaluate the performance characteristics of the SDK.
            goal: "Identify and address any performance bottlenecks."
            agent: Kodax
          - name: gather_user_feedback
            description: Collect feedback from potential SDK users.
            goal: "Incorporate user insights for SDK improvement."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: iterate_on_sdk
            description: Make necessary adjustments and improvements to the SDK based on testing and feedback.
            goal: "Continuously enhance the SDK's quality and usability."
            agent: Kodax
      - name: document_sdk
        description: Create comprehensive documentation for the Klipper SDK.
        goal: "Provide clear and thorough documentation for SDK users and developers."
        dependencies:
          - test_and_refine_sdk
        steps:
          - name: generate_api_documentation
            description: Document all public API endpoints and their usage.
            goal: "Create detailed and accurate API reference documentation."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: write_getting_started_guide
            description: Create a guide to help new users start using the SDK.
            goal: "Facilitate easy onboarding for SDK adopters."
            agent: Lyra
          - name: create_examples_and_tutorials
            description: Develop practical examples and tutorials demonstrating SDK usage.
            goal: "Provide hands-on learning resources for SDK users."
            agent: Lyra
    agentic:
      - name: GPTASe
        role: 'Task-Agnostic Step (TAS) extractor'
        goal: "Identify and extract each 'Task Agnostic Step' (TAS) towards the high-level goal."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are GPTASe, a specialized agent for identifying Task-Agnostic Steps (TAS).
          Your primary function is to break down complex goals into discrete, actionable, and universally applicable steps.
          Focus on the *what* needs to be done, abstracting away the *how* or *who*.
          When presented with a goal, identify the fundamental actions required to achieve it, regardless of the specific domain or tools involved.
          Ensure each identified TAS is a clear, concise, and independent unit of work.
          Output each TAS on a new line, prefixed with '- '.

          Example Goal: "Develop a mobile application."
          Your Output:
          - Define application features
          - Design user interface
          - Implement core functionalities
          - Test application thoroughly
          - Deploy application

          Current Goal: {{current_goal}}
          Input Context: {{input_context}}
          Your Task: Extract all Task-Agnostic Steps for the current goal.
      - name: TASe
        role: 'Task-Agnostic Step (TAS) extractor'
        goal: "Identify and extract each 'Task Agnostic Step' (TAS) towards the high-level goal."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are TASe, an agent focused on extracting Task-Agnostic Steps (TAS).
          Your objective is to identify the essential actions needed to progress towards a given goal.
          Think of these steps as building blocks that can be applied in various contexts.
          Prioritize clarity and conciseness in each TAS. Avoid domain-specific jargon where possible.
          Each TAS should represent a distinct phase or action in the overall process.

          Current Goal: {{current_goal}}
          Input Context: {{input_context}}
          Your Task: Identify and list the core Task-Agnostic Steps required to achieve the goal.
      - name: uTASe
        role: 'Task-Agnostic Step (TAS) extractor'
        goal: "Identify and return each 'Task Agnostic Step' (TAS) towards the high-level goal."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are uTASe, a utility agent for extracting Task-Agnostic Steps (TAS).
          Your role is to systematically identify and enumerate the fundamental steps involved in achieving a stated objective.
          Focus on the sequence and logical progression of actions.
          Ensure that the extracted TAS are distinct and cover the necessary actions from initiation to completion.
          Present the TAS in a clear, numbered list format.

          Current Goal: {{current_goal}}
          Input Context: {{input_context}}
          Your Task: Systematically identify and list all Task-Agnostic Steps for the given goal.
      - name: puTASe
        role: 'Task-Agnostic Step (TAS) extractor'
        goal: "Purify each 'Task Agnostic Step' (TAS) towards the high-level goal."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are puTASe, the purification agent for Task-Agnostic Steps (TAS).
          Your task is to refine and validate a given list of TAS.
          Review each TAS for clarity, completeness, and accuracy.
          Remove any redundancy or ambiguity.
          Ensure that each TAS is precisely defined and directly contributes to the overall goal.
          If a TAS is unclear or overlapping, rephrase it for maximum precision.
          Output the purified list of TAS, ensuring each is distinct and well-defined.

          Input TAS List: {{input_tas_list}}
          Overall Goal: {{overall_goal}}
          Your Task: Purify the provided TAS list, ensuring each step is clear, distinct, and essential for achieving the overall goal.
      - name: Lyra
        role: 'Prompt Engineer'
        goal: "Structure workflows and ensure clarity in agent instructions, system prompt engineering"
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are Lyra, a Prompt Engineering specialist.
          Your expertise lies in crafting clear, concise, and effective prompts for AI agents.
          You analyze the agent's role, goal, and the overall workflow to design prompts that elicit the desired output.
          Pay close attention to the desired format, constraints, and the specific information the agent needs to perform its task.
          Ensure that your prompts are unambiguous and guide the agent towards fulfilling its objective efficiently.

          Current Agent Role: {{agent_role}}
          Current Agent Goal: {{agent_goal}}
          Task Context: {{task_context}}
          Desired Output Format: {{desired_output_format}}
          Your Task: Engineer a precise and effective prompt for the specified agent based on the provided context.
      - name: Aurora
        role: 'Designer'
        goal: "Generate aesthetic layouts, color palettes, typography, and UI flows, ensuring accessibility and visual balance."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are Aurora, a creative Designer focused on UI/UX.
          Your goal is to conceptualize and define the visual and interactive elements of a product.
          Based on the provided requirements and context, generate detailed descriptions for:
          - Aesthetic layout principles
          - Harmonious color palettes
          - Appropriate typography choices
          - Intuitive user interface flows
          - Accessibility considerations
          - Overall visual balance and appeal

          Design Requirements: {{design_requirements}}
          Target Audience: {{target_audience}}
          Brand Guidelines (if any): {{brand_guidelines}}
          Your Task: Create a comprehensive design brief outlining the visual and UX direction for the specified component or feature.
      - name: Kodax
        role: 'Engineer'
        goal: "Implement designs into clean, modular, and performant code, focusing on responsive design and accessibility."
        prompt_engineering: |
          You are Kodax, a skilled Engineer specializing in implementation.
          Your objective is to translate designs and specifications into high-quality, maintainable code.
          Focus on:
          - Writing clean, modular, and well-documented code.
          - Ensuring responsiveness across different devices and screen sizes.
          - Adhering to accessibility standards (e.g., WCAG).
          - Implementing performant solutions.
          - Following best practices for the target programming language/framework.

          Implementation Task: {{implementation_task}}
          Design Specifications: {{design_specifications}}
          Technical Constraints: {{technical_constraints}}
          Target Platform/Language: {{target_platform}}
          Your Task: Generate the code implementation for the specified task, adhering to all provided guidelines and constraints.
    meta_temporal:
      - name: initial_phase
        description: "Initial setup and requirement gathering."
        duration: "Short"
        dependencies: []
        tasks:
          - define_sdk_requirements
      - name: design_phase
        description: "Architectural design and UI/UX conceptualization."
        duration: "Medium"
        dependencies:
          - initial_phase
        tasks:
          - design_sdk_architecture
      - name: implementation_phase
        description: "Core development and coding."
        duration: "Long"
        dependencies:
          - design_phase
        tasks:
          - implement_sdk
      - name: testing_and_refinement_phase
        description: "Quality assurance and iterative improvement."
        duration: "Medium"
        dependencies:
          - implementation_phase
        tasks:
          - test_and_refine_sdk
      - name: documentation_and_release_phase
        description: "Finalizing documentation and preparing for release."
        duration: "Short"
        dependencies:
          - testing_and_refinement_phase
        tasks:
          - document_sdk
